.TH "t3_mdio_change_bits" 9 "t3_mdio_change_bits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t3_mdio_change_bits \- modify the value of a PHY register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t3_mdio_change_bits
.BI "(struct cphy *phy "  ","
.BI "int mmd "  ","
.BI "int reg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int clear "  ","
.BI "unsigned int set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phy" 12
the PHY to operate on
.IP "mmd" 12
the device address
.IP "reg" 12
the register address
.IP "clear" 12
what part of the register value to mask off
.IP "set" 12
what part of the register value to set

Changes the value of a PHY register by applying a mask to its current
value and ORing the result with a new value.
